# SENTINEL Security Auditing

SENTINEL MCP tools are available for security analysis. Use them proactively when the user asks about security, vulnerabilities, audits, or code review.

## Tool Reference

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `sentinel_audit` | Full codebase security audit |
| `sentinel_surface` | Attack surface map: endpoints, auth, data exposure |
| `sentinel_trace` | Taint flow: user input → dangerous sinks |
| `sentinel_attack_graph` | Trust boundary and privilege escalation graph (Mermaid) |
| `sentinel_logic` | IDOR, BAC, business logic flaws |
| `sentinel_review` | Deep single-file security review |
| `sentinel_verify` | Confirm or dismiss a specific finding |
| `sentinel_diff` | Security impact of a git diff / PR |
| `sentinel_harden` | Hardening checklist from codebase scan |
| `sentinel_exploit_chain` | Full exploitation chain for a finding |
| `sentinel_hunt` | Fast category-focused scan (injection/auth/secrets) |
| `sentinel_rules` | List all detection rules |
| `sentinel_report` | Retrieve stored audit as markdown/json/sarif |

## When to Invoke

Trigger SENTINEL when the user asks:
- "review this code for security issues"
- "find vulnerabilities in this project"
- "is this code safe / secure?"
- "audit this directory"
- "check for SQL injection / XSS / command injection"
- "is this PR safe to merge?"
- "what's the attack surface of this app?"
- "trace where user input goes"
- "show me privilege escalation paths"

## Quick Start

```
# Full audit
sentinel_audit(target="./")

# PR review
sentinel_diff(repo_path="./", base="main")

# Single file
sentinel_review(file_path="./app/auth.py")
```
